---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service | PDF Toolkit"
  description="PDF Toolkit terms of service. Free to use, open source, MIT licensed."
  canonical="/terms"
>
  <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>Use of the service</h2>
    <p>
      PDF Toolkit is a free, open-source tool provided as-is. You may use it for any lawful purpose.
      By using this service you agree not to use it for any illegal activity or to process files
      you do not have the right to use.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranties</h2>
    <p>
      PDF Toolkit is provided without warranty of any kind. We make no guarantees about the
      accuracy, reliability, or availability of the service. You use it at your own risk.
      Always keep backups of important documents before processing them.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      All processing happens in your browser. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
      Your files never leave your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Open source</h2>
    <p>
      PDF Toolkit is open-source software licensed under the
      <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MIT License</a>.
      You are free to use, copy, modify, and distribute it subject to the terms of that license.
      The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/pdftoolkit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      The web version may display advertisements via Google AdSense. Ads help keep the service
      free. You can support us by disabling your ad blocker, or by purchasing the optional
      ad-free upgrade when it becomes available.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the service after changes
      constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
